Date: Tue, 26 Apr 2016 16:23:57 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 1297/2066] thermal: Kconfig: Remove dependency between
 RCAR_GEN3_THERMAL and CPU_THERMAL

CPU_THERMAL is only required in case of using CPU Frequency reduction
as generic CPU cooling mechanism.
Thermal sensor driver can work properly without cooling devices enabled.
This patch removes the dependency between them,
so users can be flexible on selecting CPU cooling support.

Signed-off-by: Thao Nguyen <thao.nguyen.yb@rvc.renesas.com>
[zou:Original patch taken from
git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/horms/renesas-bsp.git
 v4.9/rcar-3.5.1]
Signed-off-by: zou cao <cao.zou@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/thermal/Kconfig |    1 -
 1 files changed, 0 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/thermal/Kconfig b/drivers/thermal/Kconfig
index 8ffb59e..5f28172 100644
--- a/drivers/thermal/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/thermal/Kconfig
@@ -177,7 +177,6 @@ config RCAR_GEN3_THERMAL
 	tristate "Renesas R-Car Gen3 thermal driver"
 	depends on ARCH_RENESAS || COMPILE_TEST
 	depends on HAS_IOMEM
-	select CPU_THERMAL
 	help
 	  Enable this to plug the R-Car Gen3 thermal sensor driver into the Linux
 	  thermal framework.
